
'''* PhD dissertation: Incorporating the Commons: A Political Economic Analysis of Corporate Involvement in Free and Open Source Software Projects. By Benjamin J. Birkinbine. University of Oregon, 2014'''


=Description=

"focused on three case studies: 1) Microsoft's transition from opposition to support of open source software; 2) How Red Hat, Inc. has been able to become the largest and only publicly traded company operating solely in free software; and 3) the free and open source software community's response to Oracle's acquisition of Sun Microsystems."


